Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows two flat areas joined by a convex rounded area like from a bag or suchlike (similar to EA86732, EA86742, EA86759 and EA86762), in the break two impressions of a string of 0.2 cm width. The top bears a small part of an oval seal impression showing a seated figure, facing to the left. The rest is not preserved any more.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
